During the 1970s Baluchistan was the scene of a major uprising which was brutally put down by the government
The province has been gripped by a sporadic tribal revolt for more than a year but the violence surged after the January rape of a 32 year-old doctor at Pakistans largest gas field at Sui in Baluchistan
